The All Progressives Congress (APC) has won the presidential election in President Muhammadu Buhari’s polling unit in Katsina state. Bola Tinubu is the APC presidential candidate. At polling unit 003, ward Sarkin Yarn A, Kofar Baru Gidan Niyan in Daura where Buhari voted, APC secured 215 votes, followed by the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) with 51 votes. The New Nigeria Peoples Party (NNPP) secured 37 votes, while the Labour Party (LP) got no vote. For the senatorial seat, APC had 184 votes, 51 went to PDP, while NNPP secured four. However, for the house of representatives election in the polling unit, APC got 236 votes, PDP had 51, and NNPP got four votes.